  <name>InnStereo</name>
  <summary>A stereographic projection program</summary>

  <description>
    <p>
      InnStereo is a stereographic projection (or stereonet) program. It
      can be used to plot planes, linears and conical distributions. A
      variety of calculations can be performed, such as finding the mean
      direction, the common great-circle of a set of linears or the
      eigenvectors of a dataset. The plots can be styled in many ways
      including a dynamically generated legend and countours and colormaps.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Equal area and equal angle stereonet</li>
      <li>Dynamically plot linears, great- and small circles</li>
      <li>Layer managment</li>
      <li>Import and export CSV files</li>
      <li>Calculate eigenvectors and eigenvalues</li>
      <li>Save plot in vector formats</li>
      <li>Rotate datasets around arbitrary axes</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

